to students to help them pursue their academic and professional dreams  CME awarded dozens of scholarships to students and supports UIC in its mission to provide access to excellence and success for our students  many of whom are UIC alumnus  added personal stories to the ceremony as they detailed the scholarship requirements and the interests and accomplishments of the donors Additionally  two new scholarships were awarded from CEPAC members J  This scholarship is awarded to students in materials or civil engineering who are members of National Society of Black Engineers  with a preference for members of the Society of Women Engineers  and he was very much involved in education  We grew up on the West Side of Chicago  We were educated on the West Side of Chicago  I think my father would get a great kick out of the fact that we endowed the scholarship in his name on his side of town All of the scholarships were appreciated as students accepted them with wide smiles and a sense gratitude earned money and talents to us  Last semester  to all of you who have given money for these scholarships  They are not lost on us  and hopefully we can give back to some of your companies and the community at large Apart from receiving scholarships  the gathering provided students with a chance to meet the donor or a corporate representative of their scholarship  It also provided them with the opportunity to network CEPAC Scholarships  UIC David Staudacher Scholarship Donors and Recipients ACCESS ILLINOIS JOHN BURNETT SCHOLARSHIP  nMuntather H  Merei  Hussein A  Mohd ALFRED BENESCH SCHOLARSHIP  nLuke E  Zanoni DAVID E  BOYCE GRADUATE SCHOLARSHIP  nDongwoo Lee  Ali Shamshiripour PROFESSOR ROBERT H  BRYANT SCHOLARSHIP  nLuke E  Zanoni CHRISTOPHER B  AND SUSAN S  BURKE GRADUATE STUDENT AWARD  nMahsa Izadmehr  Girish Kumar  Fatemeh Nazari ROSEMARY BURKE SCHOLARSHIP  nMeia J  Coutre  Crystal Ramos CEPAC SCHOLARSHIP  nTanja Rakovic CLARK DIETZ SCHOLARSHIP  nOscar Rodriguez PROFESSOR EDWARD